```css
.parent {
    text-align: center; /* Center the inline elements horizontally */
}

.centered-div {
    display: inline-block; /* Ensure the div behaves like an inline element */
}
```

### 5. Using `position: absolute` and `transform`
This method is useful when you need to center an element absolutely within its parent.

```html
<div class="parent">
    <div class="centered-div">Content</div>
</div>
```

```css
.parent {
    position: relative; /* Ensure the parent is positioned */
}

.centered-div {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%); /* Center the div horizontally */
}
```

